# Feature Animation: AI Agent Showcase

Create a high-fidelity React animation using `framer-motion` to demonstrate the "AI Agent" workflow: User Chat -> AI Analysis -> Data Visualization -> Actionable CTA.

## Proposed Changes

### [Component] Feature Showcase
#### [MODIFY] [LandingFeatures.tsx](file:///c:/Users/Admin/Desktop/prod-2-adecos/src/containers/landing/LandingFeatures.tsx)
- Replace `SkeletonOne` with a new, dynamic `AIAgentPreview` component.
- The component will cycle through a repeating animation loop:
    1. **User Input Phase**: A realistic chat message slides in.
    2. **Processing Phase**: Animated typing/thinking indicator.
    3. **Visualization Phase**: Transition from chat bubbles into a functional, animated bar chart.
    4. **Action Phase**: Reveal an "Add to Dashboard" or "Export" button to show the actionable nature of the tool.

### [Component] Animation Logic
- Use **Motion Variants** for smooth transitions between "Chat Mode" and "Chart Mode".
- Implement a **Layout Animation** so the container expands/contracts naturally.
- Add **Staggered Bar Animations** for the chart reveal.

## User Review Required

> [!TIP]
> **Action Button**: For the final "Action" button, I propose using "Lưu vào dự án" (Save to Project) or "Thêm vào Dashboard" to match the app's core value proposition.

> [!NOTE]
> **Loop Timing**: I will set the loop to roughly 6-8 seconds to allow users to follow the sequence without it feeling rushed or repetitive.

